title: JUI-P Candidate Makhdoomzada Muhammad Aftab Haider wins PK-111 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Jamiat Ulma-e-Islam Pakistan’ (JUI) Candidate Makhdoomzada Muhammad Aftab Haider has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-111, D.I.Khan -I by securing 41,052 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf Parliamentarian (PTI-P) candidate Ehtesham Javed who bagged 37,008 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 60.98 per cent.
